      • fromByteBuffer

        T fromByteBuffer(ByteBuffer buffer,
               int numBytes)
        Convert values from their underlying byte representation. Implementations of this method must not change the given buffer mark, or limit, but may modify its position. Use buffer.asReadOnlyBuffer() or buffer.duplicate() if mark or limit need to be set.
        Parameters:
        buffer - buffer to read value from
        numBytes - number of bytes used to store the value, starting at buffer.position()
        Returns:
        an object created from the given byte buffer representation
